ου\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"patronym\" data-text=\"Ἡρακλείου\">ΗΡΑΚΛΕΙΟΥ\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/div>\u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"facsimile-images\">\u003Ch2>Facsimile Images\u003C/h2>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"apparatus\">\u003Ch4>Apparatus criticus\u003C/h4>\u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan>  \u003Cspan>Text according to Kaibel in IG\u003C/span>  \u003C/span>; \u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan class=\"2\">2: \u003Cspan>Gualtherus: ΑΝΑΟΑΡΧΟΝ. Bartholini: ΑΝΑΣΙΑΡΧΟΝ. Wilamowitz: Ἀνά[ξ]αρχον.\u003C/span>  \u003C/span>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"translation\">\u003Ch2>English translation\u003C/h2>\u003Cp class=\"translation-author\">\u003Ca href=\"https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0981-2465\">Matthew Hewitt\u003C/a>\u003C/p>  \u003Cp>The annointed (honour) Agatharchos, son of Herakleios.\u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"commentary\">\u003Ch2>commentary\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>The stone was seen by Gualtherus, but (contra Fuduli 2017: 176, who seems to misread Salinas' report in NSA 1880, pp. 191-195, referring a description of IG XIV.370 to this text), was no longer discoverable when Salinas visited in 1880. \u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"bibliography\">\u003Ch2>bibliography\u003C/h2>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli> Gualtherus 1624 [1625] 316 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001931\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001931\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Castelli 1769 cl.6 no.2 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002084\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002084\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Franz 1853 5609 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001250\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001250\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Kaibel 1890 \u003Ca href=\"https://clio.columbia.edu/catalog/6873760\" target=\"_blank\">369\u003C/a>  \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.